delta_rule_sm120_f32_out.patch — FP32 GDN output (o_dtype=Float32 direct store).

The GDN output is the fp32 accumulator; the stock kernel truncates it to bf16
(o_store) before the bf16 gated RMS norm — the D1 bf16-truncation loss (avarok
#248/#290). With o.dtype==float32 the host now selects a DIRECT-STORE variant:
  * o_store_direct: predicated per-element reg→gmem fp32 stores using the
    existing tOcO identity coords (StMatrix8x8x16bOp is 16-bit-only, so the
    smem path cannot carry fp32);
  * smem_o (16 KB), the o smem layout, the O TMA store atom, and the STORE_O
    warp's CollectiveStoreTma are all elided under self.o_direct — this freed
    16 KB is what lets the fp32 KK inverse patch fit under the ~99 KB sm_121a
    smem cap;
  * o_pipeline is still created but never used in direct mode (producer and
    consumer sides are both const-guarded — nobody blocks);
  * the state path is UNTOUCHED: carried-state bits must be identical between
    the bf16 and f32 legs (gdn_export_f32.py asserts state max_abs == 0.0 for
    this patch alone; the f32_inverse patch legitimately changes the state).
Default behavior (o.dtype == q.dtype) is byte-identical to the unpatched
kernel: every new code path is const-guarded on self.o_direct.

Apply AFTER delta_rule_sm120_aot_export.patch + delta_rule_sm120_sm121a.patch
(patch -p1 from /home/ms/flashinfer). Export with gdn_export_f32.py.

